<title>USA: Ashcroft will devote more time to BHI.</title>
<headline>Ashcroft will devote more time to BHI.</headline>
<dateline>NEW YORK 1997-03-18</dateline>
<text>
<p>BHI Corp said Tuesday that its chairman, Michael Ashcroft, will devote more time to BHI activities in the wake of the proposed merger between ADT Ltd and Tyco International Ltd.</p>
<p>Ashcroft is also chairman and chief executive of ADT.</p>
<p>He said that as non-executive executive chairman of BHI and shareholder of approximately 65 percent of the company, he has monitored BHI's progress and developed many contacts in Central America and the Caribbean region, where BHI has operations.</p>
<p>Ashcroft added that he will now have the time to leverage those contacts on BHI's behalf while taking a more active role in the company's operations.</p>
